==English==

===Noun===
'''[[inessive]] [[case]]'''

#{{grammar}}: noun [[case]] used to indicate location '''inside''' something. In English, this is usually expressed by the prepositions "in" or "inside," as in "inside the house." Languages that use the inessive case include [[Finnish]], [[Hungarian]], [[Estonian]], and [[Erzya]].

